(firstQuint)Unknown Cause of Acute Liver Failure.

 Methodology: Multicentric French national cohort with prospective collection of data and constitution of biobank, in patients hospitalized in a context of acute liver failure without known cause at admission.

 Follow-up during 3 months for each patients.

 The primary objective is to determine predictive factors of early mortality.

 This study is an observational cohort and patients will received standard care during the follow-up.

